news.title: Payrolls rose 22,000 in August, less than expected in further sign of hiring slowdown
news.summary: Nonfarm payrolls were expected to increase by 75,000 in August. The unemployment rate edged up tp 4.3% in the month.

news.title: Tesla's nearly $1 trillion new pay plan for Musk would expand his voting power
news.summary: Tesla shareholders will vote on whether the automaker should invest in Musk's artificial intelligence company, xAI. Tesla will also ask shareholders to vote on if the company should make an investment in SpaceX.

news.title: ‘I’m glad it’s over.’ Google CEO thanks Trump for antitrust 'resolution'
news.summary: President Donald Trump congratulated Google CEO Sundar Pichai on “big day’ following antitrust ruling. President Donald Trump congratulates Google CEOSundar Pchai on "big day" following antitrust decision.

news.title: Lutnick predicts 'better' job number accuracy after Trump fired BLS chief
news.summary: President Donald Trump declines to commit to saying BLS' upcoming jobs data will be credible. BLS releases jobs data for July on Friday.

news.title: Demand for industrial space falls for the first time in 15 years
news.summary: Economic uncertainty brought on by constantly changing tariff policy and persistently high inflation is taking a greater toll on the warehouse sector. The warehouse sector is one of the biggest contributors to the British economy.

news.title: It’s not just Lisa Cook in hot water over second homes. U.K. deputy prime minister quits over tax issue.
news.summary: Angela Rayner reportedly failed to properly pay stamp duty on second home. Rayner's second home was bought for $1.5 million in 2007.

news.title: U.S. unemployment rate jumps to nearly 4-year high. Weak 22,000 increase in August jobs report tees up Fed rate cut.
news.summary: The U.S. economy added a lackluster 22,000 new jobs in August. The unemployment rate rose to a nearly four-year high, underscoring the increasing fragility of the labor market.

news.title: Nvidia stock has been in something of a rut. One analyst says the price could double.
news.summary: Analyst says Wall Street is underestimating future data-center revenue for chip giant. Chip giant is expected to report record quarterly results this week.

news.title: Treasury bonds aren’t the safe haven they’ve been in the past — and taxpayers will pay a price
news.summary: The U.S. government faces hundreds of billions of dollars in additional interest payments. The interest payments are part of a larger plan to pay down the nation's debt.

news.title: Elon Musk could be paid $1 trillion if he makes Tesla ‘the most valuable company in history’
news.summary: Tesla proposes a $1 trillion pay package for Elon Musk, if can stay focused on adding $7.5 trillion to the company's value.
